ad extension of the scapula distal to the glenoid region that conforms to the contour of the ribs. Origin for the major shoulder muscles including the deltoid group.\" [PHENOSCAPE]\n190310: comment: In non-tetrapod sarcopterygians the role of the scapula blade is filled by the enlarge cleithrum.\n190311: is_a: UBERON:0005913 ! zone of bone organ\n190312: relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7972-3866 ! T Alexander Dececchi\n190313: relationship: part_of UBERON:0006849 ! scapula\n190314: \n190315: [Term]\n190316: id: UBERON:1500003\n190317: name: lateral line canal lumen\n190318: def: \"Anatomical space that contains a portion of the lateral line system.\" [PHENOSCAPE] {comment=\"PHENOSCAPE:MAH\"}\n190319: comment: TO DO: think about definitions for spaces in bone, in which pass through nerves, muscles, tendons and are defined by them.\n190320: is_a: UBERON:0000464 ! anatomical space\n190321: relationship: part_of UBERON:0002540 ! lateral line system\n190322: \n190323: [Term]\n190324: id: UBERON:1500005\n190325: name: ischial cartilage\n190326: def: \"Paired cartilaginous element forming the posterior portion of the pelvic girdle [D.F. Markle, BULLETIN OF MARINE SCIENCE. 30(1): 45-53. 1980].\" [PHENOSCAPE]\n190327: is_a: UBERON:0007844 ! cartilage element\n190328: relationship: develops_from UBERON:0006254 ! ischial cartilage element\n190329: relationship: part_of UBERON:0007832 ! pelvic girdle skeleton\n\n(Showing lines 190250-190329 of 226791. Use offset=190330 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: UBERON:1000024\nname: parenchyma of spleen\ndef: \"A parenchyma that is part of a spleen.\" [OBOL:automatic]\nsynonym: \"splenic parenchyma\" EXACT [FMA:16029]\nxref: FMA:16029\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000353 ! parenchyma\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002106 ! spleen\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:1100000\nname: digestive tract junction\ndef: \"An anatomical junction between two parts of the digestive tract.\" [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-