{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981299883,"sessionID":"ses_1cc7554dbffekMDE4SCKIqUIm3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"webfetch","callID":"call_CsHJJvlc4GGesvw6Zz1oKHMZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"url":"https://meshb.nlm.nih.gov/record/ui?ui=D014599","format":"markdown","timeout":60},"output":"MeSH Browser          \n\n[![NLM Logo](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/images/NLM_White.png)](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/)\n\nToggle navigation [![MeSH Logo](/public/img/meshLogo.jpg)](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/)\n\n-   [Search](/)\n-   [Tree View](/treeView)\n-   [MeSH on Demand](/MeSHonDemand)\n-   [MeSH 2025](https://meshb-prev.nlm.nih.gov/)\n-   [About](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/mbinfo.html)\n-   [Suggestions](https://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/meshsugg.html)\n-   [Contact Us](https://support.nlm.nih.gov/support/create-case/)\n\n# Uterus MeSH Descriptor Data 2026\n\n-   Details\n-   Qualifiers\n-   MeSH Tree Structures\n-   Concepts\n\n  \n\nMeSH Heading\n\nUterus\n\nTree Number(s)\n\nA05.360.319.679\n\nUnique ID\n\nD014599\n\nRDF Unique Identifier\n\n[http://id.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/D014599](https://id.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/D014599.html)\n\nAnnotation\n\n/blood supply: consider [PLACENTAL CIRCULATION](/record/ui?ui=D021041); [/‌surg](/record/ui?ui=Q000601): consider [HYSTERECTOMY](/record/ui?ui=D007044) or [HYSTEROTOMY](/record/ui?ui=D020883); inflammation = [ENDOMETRITIS](/record/ui?ui=D004716)\n\nScope Note\n\nThe hollow thick-walled muscular organ in the female [PELVIS](/record/ui?ui=D010388). It consists of the fundus which is the site of [EMBRYO IMPLANTATION](/record/ui?ui=D010064) and [FETAL DEVELOPMENT](/record/ui?ui=D047109). Beyond the isthmus at the perineal end of fundus, is [CERVIX UTERI](/record/ui?ui=D002584) (the neck) opening into [VAGINA](/record/ui?ui=D014621). Beyond the isthmi at the upper abdominal end of fundus, are the [FALLOPIAN TUBES](/record/ui?ui=D005187).\n\nEntry Term(s)\n\nFundus Uteri\n\nUteri\n\nUterine Cornua\n\nUterine Fundus\n\nUterus Cornua\n\nWomb\n\nSee Also\n\n[Hysterectomy](/record/ui?ui=D007044)\n\n[Hysterosalpingography](/record/ui?ui=D007047)\n\n[Hysteroscopy](/record/ui?ui=D015907)\n\nConsider Also\n\nconsider also terms at [HYSTER-](/search?searchInField=termDescriptor&sort=&size=20&searchType=exactMatch&searchMethod=SubString&q=HYSTER)\n\nDate Introduced\n\n1966/01/01\n\nLast Updated\n\n2018/02/06\n\n  \n\nAllowable Qualifiers\n\n-   [abnormalities (AB)](/record/ui?ui=Q000002)\n-   [anatomy & histology (AH)](/record/ui?ui=Q000033)\n-   [blood supply (BS)](/record/ui?ui=Q000098)\n-   [chemistry (CH)](/record/ui?ui=Q000737)\n-   [cytology (CY)](/record/ui?ui=Q000166)\n-   [diagnostic imaging (DG)](/record/ui?ui=Q000000981)\n-   [drug effects (DE)](/record/ui?ui=Q000187)\n-   [embryology (EM)](/record/ui?ui=Q000196)\n-   [enzymology (EN)](/record/ui?ui=Q000201)\n-   [growth & development (GD)](/record/ui?ui=Q000254)\n-   [immunology (IM)](/record/ui?ui=Q000276)\n-   [injuries (IN)](/record/ui?ui=Q000293)\n-   [innervation (IR)](/record/ui?ui=Q000294)\n-   [metabolism (ME)](/record/ui?ui=Q000378)\n-   [microbiology (MI)](/record/ui?ui=Q000382)\n-   [parasitology (PS)](/record/ui?ui=Q000469)\n-   [pathology (PA)](/record/ui?ui=Q000473)\n-   [physiology (PH)](/record/ui?ui=Q000502)\n-   [physiopathology (PP)](/record/ui?ui=Q000503)\n-   [radiation effects (RE)](/record/ui?ui=Q000528)\n-   [surgery (SU)](/record/ui?ui=Q000601)\n-   [transplantation (TR)](/record/ui?ui=Q000637)\n-   [ultrastructure (UL)](/record/ui?ui=Q000648)\n-   [virology (VI)](/record/ui?ui=Q000821)\n\n-   [Urogenital System \\[A05\\]](/record/ui?ui=D014566)\n    -   [Genitalia \\[A05.360\\]](/record/ui?ui=D005835)\n        -   [Genitalia, Female \\[A05.360.319\\]](/record/ui?ui=D005836)\n            -   [Adnexa Uteri \\[A05.360.319.114\\]](/record/ui?ui=D000290)\n            -   [**Uterus \\[A05.360.319.679\\]**](/record/ui?ui=D014599)\n                -   [Cervix Uteri \\[A05.360.319.679.256\\]](/record/ui?ui=D002584)\n          