{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981437582,"sessionID":"ses_1cc7554dbffekMDE4SCKIqUIm3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cadCKy1OzKF9SCAmSbkzQiJ9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Added the requested term and committed the change locally; changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Note: the definition PMIDs supplied in the issue (`PMID:41204538`, `PMID:40653088`) were invalid/nonexistent, so I used a validated MeSH anatomical definition source instead and kept the requested synonym source `PMID:39112955`.\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Added new term `UBERON:9900000` for `uterine fundus`.\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue requested a new anatomical structure term for the superior dome-shaped part of the uterus.\n+- Existing UBERON content already has `uterus`, `body of uterus`, `uterine cervix`, and uterine wall layers, but did not include a standalone term for the uterine fundus.\n+- The issue-supplied parentage was implemented as `is_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part` plus `relationship: part_of UBERON:0000995 ! uterus`.\n+\n+Definition and sources:\n+- I did not use the two definition PMIDs from the issue because `PMID:41204538` and `PMID:40653088` are invalid/nonexistent identifiers.\n+- I used the MeSH uterus record (`MESH:D014599`) as the definition source because it includes a narrower concept for `Uterine Fundus` with scope note: \"The superior portion of the uterus above the uterine tube line opposite to the cervix.\"\n+- I kept the requested exact synonym `fundus uteri` and retained the supplied synonym source `PMID:39112955` after validating that this PMID exists.\n+\n+Metadata added:\n+- `relationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé`\n+- `property_value: dcterms-date \"2026-05-17T00:00:00Z\" xsd:dateTime`\n+- `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3637\" xsd:anyURI`\n+- `created_by: drago